{
  "texts": [
    "Challenges emerge from the rapidly evolving technological landscape, requiring the standard to be dynamic and adaptable.",
    "Achieving consistency on a global scale is also challenging, given the variations in regulatory environments and cultural differences.",
    "Once a consensus is reached, the finalized standard is submitted to a recognized standards organization for formal approval.",
    "The approved standard, encompassing guidelines and criteria for sustainable computing, is then published and made available to the public.",
    "This standardized framework serves as a universal reference point for organizations seeking to adopt and implement environmentally responsible ing practices.Post-standardization, the critical validation phase unfolds."
  ]
}